/* gamedata-w4-rift.mjs — World 4 Rift task/tier table + Skill Mastery + Construct Mastery
 * threshold tables and formulas, extracted verbatim from N.js (v1.19-era). GENERATED by a
 * one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed); refresh after a major patch.
 *
 * SOURCE TABLE: `na.RiftStuff=\nfunction(){return[...]}` — note the literal newline in the
 * minified source between `RiftStuff=` and `function` (N.js:23820-23824); a naive single-line
 * grep for "na.RiftStuff=function" will NOT find it — search for "RiftStuff=" and
 * "function(){return[" separately, or grep across line boundaries. Registered into
 * CustomLists.h.RiftStuff at N.js:19286002-ish (`e=na.RiftStuff();b.h.RiftStuff=e;`).
 * Runtime accessor: `m._customBlock_RiftStuff=function(d,b){...}`, N.js:17868-17883.
 *
 * na.RiftStuff() returns 7 sub-arrays:
 *   [0] (16) task description templates      -> RIFT_TASK_TYPES[].desc
 *   [1] (65 = 13x5) reward milestones          -> RIFT_REWARDS (x,y,name,Filler,Filler per entry)
 *   [2] (70) cosmetic monster id per tier      -> RIFT_TIERS[].mob
 *   [3] (70) hue-rotation filter per tier      -> RIFT_TIERS[].hue
 *   [4] (100) task-TYPE index per tier         -> RIFT_TIERS[].taskType (only 0..69 modeled; 70..74
 *                                                 still task-type 9 "cannot progress", 75..99 are
 *                                                 unassigned 0 — reserved, no content built yet)
 *   [5] (16) requirement amount per task TYPE  -> RIFT_TASK_TYPES[].req
 *   [6] (14) per-milestone render flag         -> RIFT_RENDER_FLAG (meaning UNRESOLVED, see below)
 *
 * ROW-COUNT GOTCHA: the research brief assumed "~60" tiers. The verified count is **65 real,
 * individually-authored tiers** (Rift 1-65, idx 0-64) followed by **5 explicit "cannot progress
 * further" placeholder tiers** (Rift 66-70, idx 65-69, all taskType 9) baked into the same
 * 70-long cosmetic-mob/hue arrays. Beyond idx 69, the (100-long) taskType array continues with
 * more `9`s through idx 74 then `0`s (unassigned) through idx 99 — reserved future content with
 * NO cosmetic-mob/hue data to back it (those arrays stop at 70). Treat idx 70-99 as
 * not-yet-built, not as real tiers.
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

